32#ifndef _ASM_WW_MUTEX_H_
33#define _ASM_WW_MUTEX_H_
34
35#include <sys/types.h>
36#include <sys/condvar.h>
37#include <sys/mutex.h>
38#include <sys/rbtree.h>
39
40#include <linux/atomic.h>
41#include <linux/mutex.h>
42
43struct ww_class {
44 atomic64_t wwc_ticket;
45};
46
47#define DEFINE_WW_CLASS(CLASS) \
48 struct ww_class CLASS = { \
49 .wwc_ticket = ATOMIC64_INIT(0), \
50 }
51
52struct ww_acquire_ctx {
53 struct ww_class *wwx_class __diagused;
54 struct lwp *wwx_owner __diagused;
55 uint64_t wwx_ticket;
56 unsigned wwx_acquired;
57 bool wwx_acquire_done;
58 struct rb_node wwx_rb_node;
59};
60
61struct ww_mutex {
62 enum ww_mutex_state {
63 WW_UNLOCKED, /* nobody owns it */
64 WW_OWNED, /* owned by a lwp without a context */
65 WW_CTX, /* owned by a context */
66 WW_WANTOWN, /* owned by ctx, waiters w/o ctx waiting */
67 } wwm_state;
68 union {
69 struct lwp *owner;
70 struct ww_acquire_ctx *ctx;
71 } wwm_u;
72 /*
73 * XXX wwm_lock must *not* be first, so that the ww_mutex has a
74 * different address from the kmutex for LOCKDEBUG purposes.
75 */
76 kmutex_t wwm_lock;
77 struct ww_class *wwm_class;
78 struct rb_tree wwm_waiters;
79 kcondvar_t wwm_cv;
80#ifdef LOCKDEBUG
81 bool wwm_debug;
82#endif
83};
84
85/* XXX Make the nm output a little more greppable... */
86#define ww_acquire_done linux_ww_acquire_done
87#define ww_acquire_fini linux_ww_acquire_fini
88#define ww_acquire_init linux_ww_acquire_init
89#define ww_mutex_destroy linux_ww_mutex_destroy
90#define ww_mutex_init linux_ww_mutex_init
91#define ww_mutex_is_locked linux_ww_mutex_is_locked
92#define ww_mutex_lock linux_ww_mutex_lock
93#define ww_mutex_lock_interruptible linux_ww_mutex_lock_interruptible
94#define ww_mutex_lock_slow linux_ww_mutex_lock_slow
95#define ww_mutex_lock_slow_interruptible linux_ww_mutex_lock_slow_interruptible
96#define ww_mutex_trylock linux_ww_mutex_trylock
97#define ww_mutex_unlock linux_ww_mutex_unlock
98
99void ww_acquire_init(struct ww_acquire_ctx *, struct ww_class *);
100void ww_acquire_done(struct ww_acquire_ctx *);
101void ww_acquire_fini(struct ww_acquire_ctx *);
102
103void ww_mutex_init(struct ww_mutex *, struct ww_class *);
104void ww_mutex_destroy(struct ww_mutex *);
105
106/*
107 * WARNING: ww_mutex_is_locked returns true if it is locked by ANYONE.
108 * Does NOT mean `Do I hold this lock?' (answering which really
109 * requires an acquire context).
110 */
111bool ww_mutex_is_locked(struct ww_mutex *);
112
113int ww_mutex_lock(struct ww_mutex *, struct ww_acquire_ctx *);
114int ww_mutex_lock_interruptible(struct ww_mutex *,
115 struct ww_acquire_ctx *);
116void ww_mutex_lock_slow(struct ww_mutex *, struct ww_acquire_ctx *);
117int ww_mutex_lock_slow_interruptible(struct ww_mutex *,
118 struct ww_acquire_ctx *);
119int ww_mutex_trylock(struct ww_mutex *);
120void ww_mutex_unlock(struct ww_mutex *);
121
122#endif /* _ASM_WW_MUTEX_H_ */
